        "source": "corpus/Background.md",
        "section_path": "Background / 5. Counterparty risk and CVA",
        "text": "Wrong-way risk occurs when exposure to a counterparty increases as the counterparty's credit quality deteriorates.",
        "relevance": 2
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "q45",
    "qrels": [
      {
        "qrel_id": "q45_r1",
        "text": "Right-way risk occurs when exposure to a counterparty decreases as the counterparty's credit quality deteriorates.",
        "relevance": 2
      }
    ]
  },
  {
